<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>KGM:</U></B>  Knights of the Green Mist
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>N.A.T.O.:</U></B>  Norrath Alliance Treaty Organization
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Member:</U></B>  A person belonging to, and active in, the Knights of the Green Mist.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Player:</U></B>  An actual person.  This would be the Player or Account Holder (not the Character, or “toon”), who logs into the game, plays EverQuest™, and controls one or more Characters per account.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Character:</U></B>  This is who you wish you were, not who you really are.  =)
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Main Character:</U></B>  The Character that a Player uses as his primary persona within the Guild.  When people talk about you, this is who they envision – not your Alts.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Alt:</U></B>  Alternate Character – any additional Characters that a person plays or inducts into the Guild beyond his Primary Character.
	</UL>

<BR><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE="3"><B><LI><P ALIGN="justify"><U>Minimum Qualifications</U></B></FONT>
	<UL ALIGN="justify">
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<U>New Members:</U>	<B>Level 20</B> – A Surname shall be deemed to prove that Level 20 was attained at one point prior to death(s).
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<U>Existing Members (Alts):</U>	<B>Level 10</B>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<U>Special Circumstances:</U>
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		New Members wishing to join the Guild who maintain a Character other than their Main (Guild) Character, or with Characters in other Guilds (and not wanting to leave their current Guild entirely) may apply for Sponsorship upon attaining <B>Level 15</B> – after providing sufficient evidence that their other character(s) is/are at least <B>20<SUP><U>th</U></SUP> Level</B>.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Under special circumstances and as approved by the Guild Leader or Council, these Guidelines may be temporarily waived or modified, in whole or in part, except in that at no time shall a character be admitted below <B>10<SUP><U>th</U></SUP> Level</B>.  Special circumstances may include, but are not limited to:  Open Recruitment Drives; Alts who have a Main in a N.A.T.O. Guild; as approved by the Council or Guild Leader on a case-by-case basis; etc.
		</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	If in doubt, follow the <B><I>20/10 Rule</I></B>!
	</UL>

<BR><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE="3"><B><LI><P ALIGN="justify"><U>How to Become a Knight</U></B></FONT>
	<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Nomination Process:</U></B>
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		An existing Member in good standing must first nominate new prospective Members.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		The Member should have familiar knowledge of the Nominee.  This knowledge can be gained from regularly grouping with the Player, being a friend in real life, recommendation by mutual friends, in-depth conversation / interview, etc.
		</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Acceptance of Nomination:</U></B>
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Upon acceptance into the Guild, all new Members shall undergo an Indoctrination Period.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		During the Indoctrination Period, new Members shall hold the rank of and be known as a <FONT SIZE="3" FACE="Times New Roman"><B>Knight Candidate</B></FONT>.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		New Members shall remain at the rank of Knight Candidate for a period of not less than 14 consecutive days.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		<U>Exceptions:</U>
			<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			In the event a new Member brings multiple Characters into the Guild at approximately the same time or while still at the rank of Knight Candidate, each new Character shall also hold the rank of Knight Candidate for the full 14-day Indoctrination Period, or until the expiration of the Indoctrination Period of the Player’s first Character to receive a /guildinvite, whichever is shorter.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			This Indoctrination Period does not apply to existing Members who are in good standing with the Guild <B><I>and</I></B> who have attained the rank of Knight or higher.
	  			<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">				In the event an existing Member wishes to bring additional Characters into the Guild, each new Character shall hold the rank of Knight (or Knight Candidate – whichever is higher), unless specifically designated otherwise by the Council.
				</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			<B>Remember:</B>  It is the <U><I>Player</U></I>, not the <U><I>Character</U></I>, who undergoes the Indoctrination.
			</UL>
		</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Indoctrination Period:</U></B>
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		The minimum amount of time a prospective new Member will hold the rank of Knight Candidate shall be not less than 14 consecutive days.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		The maximum amount of time a new Member will be permitted remain as a Knight Candidate within the Guild is 28 consecutive days.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		If, after 14 days, the Knight Candidate is not able to satisfactorily demonstrate his or her transition into Knighthood, they shall be counseled by a Senior Officer (Knight Commander or higher – but usually their Knight Elder), at which time areas of opportunity will be identified.
			<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			The Knight Candidate should arrange regular follow-up meetings with his or her Elder (or whoever is providing guidance) for as many times following the initial 14 days which the Elder deems to be necessary.
			</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		If, upon the completion of the maximum 28 days, the Knight Candidate has not met all qualification requirements for Knighthood as set forth by the Council, or has not been able to complete the Indoctrination Period due to inability to log into or play EverQuest™, he or she may be excommunicated from the Guild (by a member of the Council or by the Guild Leader only).
		</UL>
	</UL>

<BR><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE="3"><B><LI><P ALIGN="justify"><U>Responsibilities of the Knight Candidate</U></B></FONT>
	<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	During the Indoctrination Period, it is the responsibility of the Knight Candidate to learn and demonstrate his or her knowledge of the Guild’s <A HREF="http://www.vazaelle.net/modules.php?op=modload&name=Sections&file=index&req=viewarticle&artid=1&page=1" TITLE="History of the Knights of the Green Mist" TARGET="_blank">History</A>, Policies, Organization and Chain of Command, Mission, and any other information, which may be deemed necessary by the Council to actively participate as a productive member of our Society.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	All Knight Candidates shall register at the Official Guild Website (<A HREF="http://www.vazaelle.net/" TITLE="V a z a e l l e . N E T" TARGET="_blank">http://www.vazalle.org/</A>) using their Primary Guild Character’s first name as their username.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	Knight Candidates may also be assigned tasks, quests, and/or interviews, at the discretion of the Council or Guild Leader.
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		<I>Only</I> the Council or Guild Leader may assign such tasks, although they may be passed down to the Knight Candidate via his chain of command at the lowest rank of Knight Elder.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Although optional, we try to use these tools as a means to help select only the most worthy candidates for Knighthood, particularly during seasons of Open Recruitment.
		</UL>
	</UL>

<BR><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE="3"><B><LI><P ALIGN="justify"><U>Resources Available to the Knight Candidate</U></B></FONT>
	<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	Resources available to the Knight Candidate, and all other members of the Guild, to aid in his or her transition into Knighthood and continued personal and professional development include:
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Official Guild Website (<A HREF="http://www.vazaelle.net/" TITLE="V a z a e l l e . N E T" TARGET="_blank">http://www.vazalle.org/</A>).
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Knight Candidate’s Sponsor.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Your Fellow Knights.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Chain of Command (Knight Lieutenants, Knight Commanders, Knight Elders, Knight Council).
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Guild Leader (please do not harass the Leezardbear!).
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Any other resource that may be available – be creative!
		</UL>
	</UL>

<BR><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE="3"><B><LI><P ALIGN="justify"><U>Removal from the Guild</U></B></FONT>
	<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Guild Leader:</U></B>
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		The Guild Leader may Invite, Promote, Assign, Demote, or Disband any Member of the Guild, as well as any and all associated Characters (Alts), for any reason at any time, with or without cause or warning.
		</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Knight Council:</U></B>
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Any Member of the Council may remove any Member, as well as any and all associated Characters (Alts), from the Guild at any time for abusive or disruptive behavior (Conduct Unbecoming a Knight).  This offense includes occurrences within the Guild, within a Group, or within a Zone.
			<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			It can be personally witnessed by the Council Member, reported by other players (Guild and non-Guild), or reported by a GM or Guide.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			If not personally observed, a thorough investigation should be conducted, with or without the alleged offender’s knowledge or participation.
			</UL>
		</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	Wherever possible, /LOGs should be kept and forwarded to all Council Members and the Guild Leader via private E-Mail.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	If available and deemed appropriate or necessary, additional Council Members should act as witness to the investigation – playing a silent and impartial role (observe and report) and all /LOGs distributed as above.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Knight Candidates:</U></B>
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Knight Candidates may be removed from the Guild at any time and for any reason, with or without cause or notice, by the following Officers:
			<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			Guild Leader.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			Any Council Member.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			Any Knight Elder.
			</UL>
		</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	If a Knight Elder removes a Knight Candidate from the Guild, a brief explanation of the circumstances for the removal should be sent to the Guild Leader (and/or any available Council Member in his absence) as appropriate.
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		This notification may be made via /TELL or /GUILDSAY or via E-Mail, whichever is most appropriate for the circumstances.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		If the circumstances leading to the removal are severe, this notification should be sent to the Guild Leader and all Council Members, along with all supporting /LOG files, via E-Mail ASAP.
		</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	<B><U>Member Request:</U></B>
		<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		Members can always elect to remove themselves from the Guild at any time, for any reason, with or without cause or notification.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		When possible, we ask that you let the Guild Leader know that you are leaving, and if possible, the reason(s).
			<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			All conversations with the Guild Leader are always held in the strictest of confidence, and at no time will any personal information ever be released to anyone for any reason (short of a legal court order).
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			The reason I like to know why people leave is so I can ensure that any issues within the guild that I am not aware of may be dealt with in a swift and firm manner.  I know a lot, but I don’t know anything.  And if it’s my fault, I’d like to know so I can fix myself!  =)
			</UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">		If a Member requests from an Officer assistance with removal from the Guild (some times /guildremove just doesn’t work properly), the nearest available Officer shall immediately render aid, no questions asked.
			<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			If such request is made via /tell, the Officer is held in the strictest of confidence to keep the matter private from the /guild.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">			The Guild Leader should be informed as a courtesy, but if the departing Member so wishes, notification is not necessary.
			</UL>
		</UL>
	</UL>

<BR><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE="3"><B><LI><P ALIGN="justify"><U>Re-Application for Knighthood</U></B></FONT>
	<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	Knight Candidates who are disbanded in good faith and standing (other-than disruptive behavior or serious or repeated rules violations or other such serious cause as determined by the Council or Guild Leader) are eligible to re-apply for Knighthood after a total of 14 consecutive days have elapsed from the time they were last disbanded.
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	Upon re-applying for Knighthood, the Knight Candidate is again subject to all of the Policies set forth in this section as if he or she were applying for Guild Membership for the very first time.
	</UL>

<BR><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE="3"><B><LI><P ALIGN="justify"><U>Questions / Comments / Concerns</U></B></FONT>
	<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	Contact:	Xorrin Aarikis, Guild Leader, at <A HREF="mailto:xorri&#110;&#064;&#118;azaelle.net?subject=Knights of the Green Mist" TITLE="Send E-Mail to Xorrin Aarikis, Leader of the Knights of the Green Mist!"><B>xorri&#110;&#064;&#118;azaelle.net</B></A>.
	</UL>

<BR><FONT FACE="Tahoma" SIZE="3"><B><LI><P ALIGN="justify"><U>How to Join the Knights of the Green Mist</U></B></FONT>
	<UL>
<LI><P ALIGN="justify">	Ready join the Knights of the Green Mist?  <A HREF="http://www.vazaelle.net/modules.php?op=modload&name=phpBB_14&file=index&action=newtopic&forum=34" TITLE="CLICK HERE to join the Knights of the Green Mist!"><B>CLICK HERE</B></A> to post a message in our New Members Forum.  Be sure to use your Character's name as the Subject!
	</UL>
